ocieties. Instead, the ultimate authority resides with the cooperative housing society's general body, marking a significant step towards clarity in the state's redevelopment processes.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/registrars-sub-registrars-have-no-authority-to-issue-noc-to-housing-societies-for-redevelopment/125100588?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-19492/125100588.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}